reviews.review_text: great for '88 1988 isnt my favorite year, not even close. but great sound on this one. unique show being it was the only time they played the home of the Red Wings. Roses, To Lay Me Down, and Ship Of Fools are the standouts. Blazin' Touch of Grey as well.
Happy Birthday Drummers Oddly, I've seen shows on both drummers birthdays. Once at least possibly more than one time. Bill's on May 9 and Mickey's on September 11.

I'm sure if I listened to this I would love it.
Tough crowd
